headline: Is PayPal a Bargain After Five Year 65% Drop and New Innovation Push?
summary: If you’ve found yourself staring at PayPal Holdings’ stock ticker, wondering whether it’s time to buy, hold, or revisit your outlook, you’re far from alone. The company’s share price has spent the past twelve months in the spotlight for all the dramatic wrong reasons, slipping by roughly 14.5% over the last year and an eye-popping 65.5% over the past five years. headline: AWS outage resolved: Which companies were affected the most?
summary: Everything from apps and website hosting to even your child's schoolwork portal were affected by Amazon's (AMZN) AWS outage on Monday. The company has since announced that the Amazon Web Services' cloud outage has been resolved. Yahoo Finance tech editor Dan Howley comes on the Morning Brief to highlight an assortment of companies and platforms most affected by the outage. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.
